"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The np.sinc function does not return 1 at x=0 and 0 at x=1. The np.sinc function returns sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) at x. At x=0, it returns 1 and at x=1, it returns sin(pi)/(pi) which is close to zero but not exactly zero due to floating point precision.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7c7\\n<assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n---\\n>assert np.isclose(sinc_result[0], 1), \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n8c8\\n<assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n>assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], 0), \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\"\n}"